news.title: NOC, registration must for extracting groundwater in Noida
news.para: The administration has made it clear that strict punitive action will be taken against entities failing to register or obtain NOCs for groundwater extraction.

news.title: Large cement makers report volume growth in Q4 2025
news.para: Leading listed cement firms like UltraTech, Ambuja Cements, ACC, Shree Cements, and Dalmia Bharat have retained around 7 to 7.5 per cent growth for the cement industry in FY26, following government spending on infrastructure projects and rural recovery.

news.title: Chennai development body plans to transform Chengalpet town
news.para: To realise this, CMDA floated tenders for preparing a comprehensive development plan for Chengalpet New Town, mapping its growth from 2025 to 2045.

news.title: Ludhiana Improvement Trust seeks land for new schemes
news.para: With the trust handing over its remaining residential areas to the municipal corporation, and the MC starting the process of adopting these colonies, the trust faces a struggle for existence.

news.title: SC appointed committee approves housing project in Vasant Kunj with tree rider
news.para: The private developer has been asked to plant 250 indigenous tree species for a green fencing. Additionally, the developer is required to plant another 250 trees along the internal roadway.

news.title: No protest within a 100 meter radius of Jaypee Infratech's main office: Noida court
news.para: The ex-parte order drew sharp criticism from homebuyers, who accused the developer of misusing the legal process to suppress ‘legitimate concerns' over their flats that have been stalled for more than a decade now.

news.title: New home prices in China down 4% year-on-year in April 2025
news.para: New home prices have shown no growth since May 2023 as China attempts to lift the real estate sector, once a key driver of the economy, from a prolonged slump.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government launches Naksha to revolutionize urban planning and property taxation
news.para: The Centre, which is sponsoring Naksha programme, has picked 10 municipalities under pilot project following the state govt's request. While the aerial survey was completed in eight of the ten municipalities, aerial survey is going on in Eluru and Mangalagir-Tadepalli municipal corporations.

news.title: Rajasthan government finalises plots for M-sand units to boost legal mining
news.para: Of these, 77 plots spread over approximately 158 hectares are earmarked for M-sand production, while 32 plots covering around 131 hectares are designated for overburden dumping. All are being prepared for e-auction.

news.title: Seven more FIRs against Ansal API in land scam case
news.para: In the fresh cases, it has been alleged that the company defrauded victims of more than Rs 1.06 crore in the name of plots and flats.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA eyes private investment for land development project
news.para: ​VMRDA recently held a meeting with private developers from CREDAI and NAREDCO, during which it highlighted the advantages of the site. The land alone is valued at approximately Rs 500 crore.

news.title: Delhi master plan 2041 to be implemented soon, 48 villages to get urbanised: PWD minister
news.para: ​​The minister also announced that the first registry of properties falling under the Lal Dora category will be completely free of cost.

news.title: Centre to build 3.76 lakh homes in Assam in FY26: Rural minister
news.para: ​Addressing an event in which 55,000 houses built across Assam under the PM Awas Yojana - Gramin (PMAY-G) were handed over to the beneficiaries, Chouhan underlined the need for empowering women.

news.title: BirlaNu loss widens to ₹24.71 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: BirlaNu's net consolidated total income stood at ₹939.85 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 8.93 per cent from ₹862.78 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Consider plea to prevent illegal sand mining in Madurai village: Madras HC
news.para: The court was hearing a public interest litigation filed by N Kesirajan, a farmer, and a resident of Keeranur village in Melur taluk.

news.title: Taapsee Pannu, sister buys apartment in Mumbai for ₹4.33 crore
news.para: The apartment with a carpet area of 1,390 sq ft (129 sq meters) and a built-up area of 1,669 sq ft (155.02 sq meters) is located in Imperial Heights. It comes with a total of two car parking spaces.

news.title: Jaipur development body forms committee to verify Sirsi Road pattas
news.para: "The committee has been formed to determine the status of only those residents who managed to show us the pattas issued by the erstwhile Jhotwara Panchayat," said an official.

news.title: ED seeks more information on three survey numbers from Mysuru development body
news.para: MUDA authorities have told TOI that they are in the process of providing the required information about the properties to ED's Bengaluru office.

news.title: Signature Global lines up ₹1,200–1,500 crore to acquire land in FY26
news.para: Signature Global exceeded its FY25 pre-sales guidance by clocking ₹2,290 crore, up from the projected ₹2,000 crore. It now plans to launch projects worth ₹17,000 crore in FY26 across key micro-markets.

news.title: Delhi likely to have 200 zero waste colonies by May 2027
news.para: Currently, Delhi has 633 certified zero waste areas, including 593 colonies, group housing societies, residents' welfare associations (RWAs) and 40 institutes, collectively segregating and processing compost waste of around 100 tonnes on a daily basis.
